 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# PDE: wave equation\n",
    "### phys481 week10\n",
    "\n",
    "Much of the material in these notes is taken from the following source:\n",
    "\n",
    "       Finite Difference Computing with PDEs\n",
    "   \n",
    "       https://hplgit.github.io/fdm-book/doc/pub/book/sphinx/index.html\n",
    "       \n",
    "       \n",
    "## Introduction\n",
    "There are many interesting systems for which the variation of an important physical quantity $u$ can be accurately modelled with a one dimensional _wave equation_\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\frac{\\partial^2 u}{\\partial t^2} =\n",
    "    c^2 \\frac{\\partial^2 u}{\\partial x^2}, \\quad x\\in (0,L),\\ t\\in (0,T] $$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $c$ is a characteristic propagation speed.\n",
    "\n",
    "This partial differential equation (PDE) is second order in time, so we require two sets of initial conditions in order to fully specify it.  These are typically chosen to be some profile $I(x)$ at $t=0$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ u(x,0) = I(x), \\quad x\\in [0,L] $$\n",
    "\n",
    "and the corresponding initial time derivative $I'(x)$ also at $t=0$.  \n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial t}u(x,0) = V(x), \\quad x\\in [0,L] $$\n",
    "\n",
    "We often also need to consider spatial boundary conditions.  These are usually located at the outer edges of some region of interest.  \n",
    "\n",
    "$$ u(0,t)  = 0, \\quad  t\\in (0,T] $$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ u(L,t)  = 0, \\quad  t\\in (0,T] $$\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Discretization\n",
    "\n",
    "Numerical solutions to the wave equation can be obtained by replacing continuous derivatives with discrete differences.  Using centered second differences \n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\frac{u_i^{n+1} - 2u_i^n + u^{n-1}_i}{\\Delta t^2} =\n",
    "    c^2\\frac{u_{i+1}^{n} - 2u_i^n + u^{n}_{i-1}}{\\Delta x^2}  $$\n",
    "\n",
    "provides an explicit expression for future values \n",
    "\n",
    " $$u(x_i,t_{n+1}) = u^{n+1}_i$$\n",
    " \n",
    "at any location in terms of current and previous values\n",
    "\n",
    " $$ u^{n+1}_i = -u^{n-1}_i + 2u^n_i + C^2\n",
    "    \\left(u^{n}_{i+1}-2u^{n}_{i} + u^{n}_{i-1}\\right) $$\n",
    "\n",
    " <img src=\"https://hplgit.github.io/fdm-book/doc/pub/book/sphinx/_images/stencil_n_interior.png\">\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Speed of information\n",
    "\n",
    "It is important to note that this difference equation depends on a dimensionless parameter $C$ which is a product of the intrinsic propagation speed $c$ with the ratio of grid steps in time $\\Delta t$ and space $\\Delta x$. \n",
    "\n",
    "$$ C = c\\frac{\\Delta t}{\\Delta x} $$\n",
    "\n",
    "When $C>1$ the largest effective numerical propagation speed is less than the physical speed, typically leading to inaccurate results.\n",
    "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Courant%E2%80%93Friedrichs%E2%80%93Lewy_condition"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, when system is initially static $I'=0$ \n",
    "\n",
    "  $$ I' =  \\frac{u_i^{n+1} - u^{n-1}_i}{2 \\Delta t} = 0 $$\n",
    "  \n",
    "  $$ {u_i^{n+1} = u^{n-1}_i} $$  \n",
    "\n",
    "the first step doesn't require information about $t<0$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ u_i^1 = u^0_i - \\frac{1}{2}\n",
    "    C^2\\left(u^{0}_{i+1}-2u^{0}_{i} + u^{0}_{i-1}\\right) $$\n",
    "    \n",
    "while it is only slightly harder to deal with more general non-zero initial first derivatives.\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"https://hplgit.github.io/fdm-book/doc/pub/book/sphinx/_images/stencil_n0_interior.png\">"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# load useful libraries\n",
    "#\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "from matplotlib import animation, rc\n",
    "from IPython.display import HTML"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def wave_stepper(u, Courant=0.1, nsteps=99, save_stride=9, boundary_hack=False):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Explicit time steps of the dimensionless wave equation. \n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    C2 = Courant**2    \n",
    "    u1 = 1*u.copy()  # current displacement\n",
    "    u2 = 0*u.copy()  # future \n",
    "\n",
    "    # spatial second derivative difference equation assuming \n",
    "    # cyclic (\"wrap-around\") boundaries\n",
    "    d2u = lambda u: np.roll(u,-1) - 2*u + np.roll(u,+1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    u0 = u.copy()  #previous displacement if initial velocity is zero\n",
    "    term2 = d2u(u1)\n",
    "    u0 = u1 + 0.5*C2*term2\n",
    "    \n",
    "    result = []\n",
    "    for n in range(nsteps):        \n",
    "        term2 = d2u(u1) \n",
    "        u2 = 2*u1 - u0 + C2*term2        \n",
    "        \n",
    "        if boundary_hack:\n",
    "            u2[0], u2[-1] = 0, 0\n",
    "                 \n",
    "        u0 = u1[:]  # previous = current\n",
    "        u1 = u2[:]  # current = next\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # save results at every 9th time step for analysis and display\n",
    "        if (n%save_stride)==0: result.append(u1.copy())\n",
    "    \n",
    "    result.append(u1)\n",
    "    return result\n",
    "\n",
    "#x = np.linspace(0.0, 2.0, 199)\n",
    "#y0 = np.exp( -((x-0.8)*10)**2 )\n",
    "#nsteps=999\n",
    "#\n",
    "#yy = wave_stepper(y0, Courant=0.25, nsteps=nsteps, save_stride=20)\n",
    "#xx, my = np.meshgrid( x, np.arange(len(yy)) )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def wave_solver(u, xstep, tstep, wave_speed=1.0, save_stride=1, boundary_hack=False):\n",
    "    \"\"\" Explicit physical solution of the wave equation.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    dt = tstep[1] - tstep[0]\n",
    "    dx = xstep[1] - xstep[0]\n",
    "    C = wave_speed * dt / dx\n",
    "    if (C>0.95):\n",
    "        print('Warning- large Courant number: '+str(C)[0:4])\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return wave_stepper(u, C, len(tstep)-1, save_stride=save_stride, boundary_hack=boundary_hack ), C"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Gaussian pulse\n",
    "\n",
    "Consider an initial perturbation with a stationary Gaussian profile.  Like a stone dropped into water, this should produce waves travelling away from the source location."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "t = np.linspace(0.0, 3.0, 999)\n",
    "x = np.linspace(0.0, 2.0, 199)\n",
    "y0 = np.exp( -((x-0.8)*10)**2 )  # initial perturbation\n",
    "yy, C = wave_solver(y0, x, t, boundary_hack=False)\n",
    "yy = np.array(yy).T\n",
    "xx,tt = np.meshgrid( x, t )"
   ]
  },

    "### Animation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "\n",
       "<link rel=\"stylesheet\"\n",
       "href=\"https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.4.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\">\n",
       "<script language=\"javascript\">\n",
       "  function isInternetExplorer() {\n",
       "    ua = navigator.userAgent;\n",
       "    /* MSIE used to detect old browsers and Trident used to newer ones*/\n",
       "    return ua.indexOf(\"MSIE \") > -1 || ua.indexOf(\"Trident/\") > -1;\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  /* Define the Animation class */\n",
       "  function Animation(frames, img_id, slider_id, interval, loop_select_id){\n",
       "    this.img_id = img_id;\n",
       "    this.slider_id = slider_id;\n",
       "    this.loop_select_id = loop_select_id;\n",
       "    this.interval = interval;\n",
       "    this.current_frame = 0;\n",
       "    this.direction = 0;\n",
       "    this.timer = null;\n",
       "    this.frames = new Array(frames.length);\n",
       "\n",
       "    for (var i=0; i<frames.length; i++)\n",
       "    {\n",
       "     this.frames[i] = new Image();\n",
       "     this.frames[i].src = frames[i];\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    var slider = document.getElementById(this.slider_id);\n",
       "    slider.max = this.frames.length - 1;\n",
       "    if (isInternetExplorer()) {\n",
       "        // switch from oninput to onchange because IE <= 11 does not conform\n",
       "        // with W3C specification. It ignores oninput and onchange behaves\n",
       "        // like oninput. In contrast, Microsoft Edge behaves correctly.\n",
       "        slider.setAttribute('onchange', slider.getAttribute('oninput'));\n",
       "        slider.setAttribute('oninput', null);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    this.set_frame(this.current_frame);\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.get_loop_state = function(){\n",
       "    var button_group = document[this.loop_select_id].state;\n",
       "    for (var i = 0; i < button_group.length; i++) {\n",
       "        var button = button_group[i];\n",
       "        if (button.checked) {\n",
       "            return button.value;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    return undefined;\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.set_frame = function(frame){\n",
       "    this.current_frame = frame;\n",
       "    document.getElementById(this.img_id).src =\n",
       "            this.frames[this.current_frame].src;\n",
       "    document.getElementById(this.slider_id).value = this.current_frame;\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.next_frame = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.set_frame(Math.min(this.frames.length - 1, this.current_frame + 1));\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.previous_frame = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.set_frame(Math.max(0, this.current_frame - 1));\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.first_frame = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.set_frame(0);\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.last_frame = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.set_frame(this.frames.length - 1);\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.slower = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.interval /= 0.7;\n",
       "    if(this.direction > 0){this.play_animation();}\n",
       "    else if(this.direction < 0){this.reverse_animation();}\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.faster = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.interval *= 0.7;\n",
       "    if(this.direction > 0){this.play_animation();}\n",
       "    else if(this.direction < 0){this.reverse_animation();}\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.anim_step_forward = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.current_frame += 1;\n",
       "    if(this.current_frame < this.frames.length){\n",
       "      this.set_frame(this.current_frame);\n",
       "    }else{\n",
       "      var loop_state = this.get_loop_state();\n",
       "      if(loop_state == \"loop\"){\n",
       "        this.first_frame();\n",
       "      }else if(loop_state == \"reflect\"){\n",
       "        this.last_frame();\n",
       "        this.reverse_animation();\n",
       "      }else{\n",
       "        this.pause_animation();\n",
       "        this.last_frame();\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.anim_step_reverse = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.current_frame -= 1;\n",
       "    if(this.current_frame >= 0){\n",
       "      this.set_frame(this.current_frame);\n",
       "    }else{\n",
       "      var loop_state = this.get_loop_state();\n",
       "      if(loop_state == \"loop\"){\n",
       "        this.last_frame();\n",
       "      }else if(loop_state == \"reflect\"){\n",
       "        this.first_frame();\n",
       "        this.play_animation();\n",
       "      }else{\n",
       "        this.pause_animation();\n",
       "        this.first_frame();\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.pause_animation = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.direction = 0;\n",
       "    if (this.timer){\n",
       "      clearInterval(this.timer);\n",
       "      this.timer = null;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.play_animation = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.pause_animation();\n",
       "    this.direction = 1;\n",
       "    var t = this;\n",
       "    if (!this.timer) this.timer = setInterval(function() {\n",
       "        t.anim_step_forward();\n",
       "    }, this.interval);\n",
       "  }\n",
       "\n",
       "  Animation.prototype.reverse_animation = function()\n",
       "  {\n",
       "    this.pause_animation();\n",
       "    this.direction = -1;\n",
       "    var t = this;\n",
       "    if (!this.timer) this.timer = setInterval(function() {\n",
       "        t.anim_step_reverse();\n",
       "    }, this.interval);\n",
       "  }\n",
       "</script>\n",
       "\n",
       "<style>\n",
       ".animation {\n",
       "    display: inline-block;\n",
       "    text-align: center;\n",
       "}\n",
       "input[type=range].anim-slider {\n",
       "    width: 374px;\n",
       "    margin-left: auto;\n",
       "    margin-right: auto;\n",
       "}\n",
       ".anim-buttons {\n",
       "    margin: 8px 0px;\n",
       "}\n",
       ".anim-buttons button {\n",
       "    padding: 0;\n",
       "    width: 36px;\n",
       "}\n",
       ".anim-state label {\n",
       "    margin-right: 8px;\n",
       "}\n",
       ".anim-state input {\n",
       "    margin: 0;\n",
       "    vertical-align: middle;\n",
       "}\n",
       "</style>\n",
       "\n",
       "<div class=\"animation\">\n",
       "  <img id=\"_anim_imga785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25\">\n",
       "  <div class=\"anim-controls\">\n",
       "    <input id=\"_anim_slidera785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25\" type=\"range\" class=\"anim-slider\"\n",
       "           name=\"points\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"1\" value=\"0\"\n",
       "           oninput=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.set_frame(parseInt(this.value));\"></input>\n",
       "    <div class=\"anim-buttons\">\n",
       "      <button title=\"Decrease speed\" aria-label=\"Decrease speed\" onclick=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.slower()\">\n",
       "          <i class=\"fa fa-minus\"></i></button>\n",
       "      <button title=\"First frame\" aria-label=\"First frame\" onclick=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.first_frame()\">\n",
       "        <i class=\"fa fa-fast-backward\"></i></button>\n",
       "      <button title=\"Previous frame\" aria-label=\"Previous frame\" onclick=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.previous_frame()\">\n",
       "          <i class=\"fa fa-step-backward\"></i></button>\n",
       "      <button title=\"Play backwards\" aria-label=\"Play backwards\" onclick=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.reverse_animation()\">\n",
       "          <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-flip-horizontal\"></i></button>\n",
       "      <button title=\"Pause\" aria-label=\"Pause\" onclick=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.pause_animation()\">\n",
       "          <i class=\"fa fa-pause\"></i></button>\n",
       "      <button title=\"Play\" aria-label=\"Play\" onclick=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.play_animation()\">\n",
       "          <i class=\"fa fa-play\"></i></button>\n",
       "      <button title=\"Next frame\" aria-label=\"Next frame\" onclick=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.next_frame()\">\n",
       "          <i class=\"fa fa-step-forward\"></i></button>\n",
       "      <button title=\"Last frame\" aria-label=\"Last frame\" onclick=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.last_frame()\">\n",
       "          <i class=\"fa fa-fast-forward\"></i></button>\n",
       "      <button title=\"Increase speed\" aria-label=\"Increase speed\" onclick=\"anima785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25.faster()\">\n",
       "          <i class=\"fa fa-plus\"></i></button>\n",
       "    </div>\n",
       "    <form title=\"Repetition mode\" aria-label=\"Repetition mode\" action=\"#n\" name=\"_anim_loop_selecta785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25\"\n",
       "          class=\"anim-state\">\n",
       "      <input type=\"radio\" name=\"state\" value=\"once\" id=\"_anim_radio1_a785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25\"\n",
       "             >\n",
       "      <label for=\"_anim_radio1_a785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25\">Once</label>\n",
       "      <input type=\"radio\" name=\"state\" value=\"loop\" id=\"_anim_radio2_a785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25\"\n",
       "             checked>\n",
       "      <label for=\"_anim_radio2_a785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25\">Loop</label>\n",
       "      <input type=\"radio\" name=\"state\" value=\"reflect\" id=\"_anim_radio3_a785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25\"\n",
       "             >\n",
       "      <label for=\"_anim_radio3_a785bc9664fb4fcaa4475055eb746e25\">Reflect</label>\n",
       "    </form>\n",
       "  </div>\n",
       "</div>\n",
       "\n",
       "\n",
       "<script language=\"javascript\">\n",
       "  /* Instantiate the Animation class. */\n",
       "  /* The IDs given should match those used in the template above. */\n",

    "\n",

    "    return (line,)\n",

    "### Wave speed slope\n",
    "\n",
    "A perturbation will move at the speed of propagation $c$ and will appear as a straight line with slope $1/c$ on an $x$ verus $t$ plot."
   ]

   "source": [
    "### Energy conservation\n",
    "\n",
    "Solutions to the wave equation are conservative.  The total energy at any given time will be the sum of two quadratic terms\n",
    "\n",
    "  $$ E(t):= \\frac{1}{2}\\int_0^L \\left[ u_t^2(x,t) + c^2 u_x^2(x,t) \\right] dx $$\n",
    "  \n",
    "which correspond to the kinetic and potential energies respectively.\n",
    "\n",
    "*Task \\#1*: write a Python function to calculate the energies as a function of time for the 1-d wave equation with cyclic boundary conditions\n",
    "\n",
    "    eg.  KE,PE = wave_energies(x, t, c, u0)\n",
    "\n",
    "*Task \\#2*: calculate and plot the energies for the following parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "    c = 0.3\n",
    "    t = np.linspace(0.0, 3.0, 999)\n",
    "    x = np.linspace(0.0, 2.0, 199)\n",
    "    u0 = np.exp( -((x-0.8)*10)**2 )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Is total energy conserved?  Discuss.\n",
    "     \n",
    "*Task \\#3*: The `wave_stepper` function defaults to using cyclic boundary conditions, but has a keyword option which effectively absorbs waves at the boundaries:\n",
    "\n",
    "        if boundary_hack:\n",
    "            u2[0], u2[-1] = 0, 0\n",
    "            \n",
    "Modify wave_stepper to include perfectly reflecting boundaries and check whether energy is conserved."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Optional material\n",
    "\n",
    "### standing waves\n",
    "\n",
    "Standing waves arise from an initial condition\n",
    "\n",
    " $$u(x,0)= A \\sin\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{L}mx\\right)$$\n",
    " \n",
    "where $m$ is an integer and A is a freely chosen amplitude. The corresponding exact solution as a function of $x$ and $t$\n",
    "\n",
    " $${u_{\\small\\mbox{e}}}(x,t) =  A\\sin\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{L}{m}x\\right)\n",
    "\\cos\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{L}{m}{c}t\\right){\\thinspace .}$$\n",
    " \n",
    "must satisfy the wave equation.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "<b>It is interesting to simulate a standing wave on [0,L] and determine the error in the simulation as a function of time and location.</b>  Any choices for $A$ and $m$ should work, but simple values (ie. $A=1$ and $m=1$) might be best.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "http://hplgit.github.io/num-methods-for-PDEs/doc/pub/wave/sphinx/index.html\n",
    "\n",
    "https://ocw.mit.edu/courses/mathematics/18-303-linear-partial-differential-equations-fall-2006/lecture-notes/waveeqni.pdf\n",
    "\n",
    "http://louistiao.me/posts/notebooks/embedding-matplotlib-animations-in-jupyter-as-interactive-javascript-widgets/"
   ]
